{"title": "mcerp", "access": "public", "summary": "Real-time latin-hypercube-sampling-based Monte Carlo Error Propagation", "updated": "2020-02-15", "detail": {"meta": {"license": "BSD-3-Clause", "license_url": "http://opensource.org/search/node/BSD-3-Clause", "home": "https://github.com/tisimst/mcerp", "home_url": "https://github.com/tisimst/mcerp", "documentation": "https://github.com/tisimst/mcerp/tree/master/doc", "documentation_url": "https://github.com/tisimst/mcerp/tree/master/doc", "development": "https://github.com/tisimst/mcerp", "development_url": "https://github.com/tisimst/mcerp", "download_count": 1331, "last_upload": "Last upload: 2 months and 12 days ago"}, "installers": ["conda install -c conda-forge mcerp", "conda install -c conda-forge/label/cf202003 mcerp"], "note": " This package contains files in non-standard\n           labels", "platform_versions": [["\n  ", "v0.12"]], "description": "<div class=\"panel\">\n      <h3>Description</h3>\n      \n        \n        <div><p><code>mcerp</code> is a stochastic calculator for <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monte_Carlo_method\">Monte Carlo methods</a> that uses\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin_hypercube_sampling\">latin-hypercube sampling</a>\nto perform non-order specific <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Propagation_of_uncertainty\">error propagation</a>\n(or uncertainty analysis).</p>\n\n<p>With this package you can <strong>easily</strong> and <strong>transparently</strong> track the effects\nof uncertainty through mathematical calculations. Advanced mathematical\nfunctions, similar to those in the standard <a href=\"http://docs.python.org/library/math.html\"><code>math</code></a>\nmodule, and statistical functions like those in the <a href=\"http://docs.scipy.org/doc/scipy/reference/stats.html\"><code>scipy.stats</code></a>\nmodule, can also be evaluated directly.</p>\n\n<p>If you are familiar with Excel-based risk analysis programs like <em>@Risk</em>,\n<em>Crystal Ball</em>, <em>ModelRisk</em>, etc., this package <strong>will work wonders</strong> for you\n(and probably even be faster!) and give you more modelling flexibility with\nthe powerful Python language. This package also <em>doesn't cost a penny</em>,\ncompared to those commercial packages which cost <em>thousands of dollars</em> for a\nsingle-seat license. Feel free to copy and redistribute this package as much\nas you desire!</p>\n</div>\n        \n      \n      \n    </div>", "files": [{"type": "conda", "size": "23.9 kB", "file": {"name": "noarch/mcerp-0.12-py_1.tar.bz2", "href": "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/mcerp/0.12/download/noarch/mcerp-0.12-py_1.tar.bz2"}, "uploaded": null, "uploader": "conda-forge", "downloads": 177, "labels": [{"name": "main", "label": "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/repo/files?type=any&label=main"}, {"name": "cf202003", "label": "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/repo/files?type=any&label=cf202003"}]}, {"type": "conda", "size": "23.6 kB", "file": {"name": "noarch/mcerp-0.12-py_0.tar.bz2", "href": "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/mcerp/0.12/download/noarch/mcerp-0.12-py_0.tar.bz2"}, "uploaded": null, "uploader": "conda-forge", "downloads": 1154, "labels": [{"name": "main", "label": "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/repo/files?type=any&label=main"}, {"name": "cf202003", "label": "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/repo/files?type=any&label=cf202003"}]}], "labels": [{"name": "", "label": "0.12"}, {"name": "", "label": "0.12"}], "badges": ["https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/mcerp/badges/version.svg", "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/mcerp/badges/latest_release_date.svg", "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/mcerp/badges/latest_release_relative_date.svg", "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/mcerp/badges/platforms.svg", "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/mcerp/badges/license.svg", "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/mcerp/badges/downloads.svg", "https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/mcerp/badges/installer/conda.svg"]}}